For the salad, place the goats' cheese, chopped chillies and spinach into a large bowl and mix.Place the lemon juice, olive oil, honey and seasoning into a small bowl and whisk well. Pour over the salad and mix again.For the chicken, place the chicken strips into a small bowl, add the cumin, chilli flakes, coriander seeds, chillies and half of the olive oil, mix well and leave to marinate for ten minutes.Heat the remaining olive oil in a frying pan, add the chicken and pan fry for 3-4 minutes, or until cooked through.Add the soy sauce and Worchestershire sauce and cook for one minute.To serve, pile the salad onto a serving plate and top with the chicken.